Systemd Commands
*****************************
Systemd is a service and system manager used in linux,it helps administrators manage
like services,processors,boot opeerations,logs,system state

the main command used in systemd is
 
 "systemctl"

1.Start the Service
  
  command : systemctl start service-name

  example : systemctl start jenkins
2.Check the Status

 command : systemctl status service-name

 example : systemctl status jenkins

 if you want to direct move to the next page without using 'q'

 command : systemctl status service-name --no-page

 example : systemctl status jenkins --no-page

3.Stop a Service

 command : systemctl stop service-name
 
 example : systemctl stop jenkins

4.Restart the Service
 
 command : systemctl restart service-name

 example : systemctl restart docker

5.Enable the Service at boot
 
 command : systemctl enable service-name

 example : systemctl enable nginx

6.Disable the Service at boot
 
 command : systemctl disable service name

 example : systemctl disable jenkins

7.Reload the Service
 
 command : systemctl reload service-name

 example : systemctl reload jenkins

8.Check if the Service is active

 command : systemctl is-active service-name

 example : systemctl is-active jenkins

9.Check if the service is enable 

 command : systemctl is-enable service-name

 example : systemctl is-enable jenkins

10.Check the failed services in the system

 command : systemctl --failed

11. Show the logs avaliable sevices

 command : journalctl -u service-name

 example : journalctl -u docker

12.Shows the live system logs 
 
 command : journalctl -f

 





